(fixes #1128)
The current implementation of `rank(::QRPivoted)` is slow and inefficient because of repeated calls to `A.R`, each of which triggers memory allocation. This PR fixes that by using `A.factors` instead, which does not cause memory allocations. The proposed implementation is orders of magnitude faster and avoids unnecessary memory allocations altogether.","distinct":true,"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/LinearAlgebra.jl/commits/f13f9405a98ddda3f0268da05c44fc07842f9977"}]}

